    <h1>Venezuela Economy in {{ current_year }}: GDP, Inflation &amp; Post-Sanctions Outlook</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      After the worst peacetime economic collapse in modern history&mdash;a 75%
      contraction in GDP between 2014 and 2021&mdash;Venezuela&rsquo;s economy
      is staging a fragile recovery, driven by de facto dollarization, partial
      sanctions relief, and a political transition that has reopened the door to
      foreign investment.
    </p>
  </header>

  {# ============ Key Economic Indicators ============ #}
  <div class="stat-grid">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-num">~$100B</div>
